      <processinfo id="aspace_497d8df44842697dabf6922e88f406a6">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_43e4fe7a6ef9dae48cbba83f66cd60b2">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of research guides, inventories, and related materials documenting accessions, projects, and collections of the Department of Manuscripts and Archives at Yale University Library.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
